-- BRICS leaders create emergency reserve fund, development bank
-- By Alonso Soto
-- Tue Jul 15, 2014 02:27PM EDT
-- None



FORTALEZA, Brazil, July 15 (Reuters) - The leaders of the group of five BRICS emerging market countries signed on Tuesday a deal to create a new development bank and an emergency reserve fund, Brazil's President Dilma Rousseff announced at a summit of the group in the Brazilian city of Fortaleza.

